expected: <name>                    creates a new branch with given name; if the branch already exists, this command will fail
-h, --help                shows this help message and exits
-f, --force               forces creation of new branch even, if it already exists

-l, --list [<pattern>...] lists known branches; if any shell wildcard pattern is present, it only shows branches matching the pattern(s); when multiple patterns are given, if any of them matches, the branch is shown
-d, --delete <name>...    deletes existing branches with given names
--show-current            prints the name of the current branch; in detached HEAD state, nothing is printed
-q, --quiet               suppresses non-error messages, when creating or deleting a branch
--color <when>            uses color in output; <when> is 'never', 'always', or 'auto'
